&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary responsibilities of the &lt;strong&gt;Audio Visual Technician&lt;/strong&gt; are to operate production equipment and provide technical support for breakouts, classes, training, as well as events and/or weekend experiences.This position requires problem solving aptitude, flexibility and may require working evenings, weekends and/or holidays. This position also requires travel between multiple Christ Fellowship locations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with the Central Production Manager to provide support for scheduled events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conference / Classroom setup and management / troubleshooting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audio / Video equipment setup for outdoor environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnering with location Production Managers to provide technical assistance during weekend experiences and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending CF staff meetings, debrief meetings, and additional meetings as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Filling out regular quality reports on events/services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High School Diploma or GED&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-2 years of experience working with audio visual equipment in a theater or event setting, or a degree in a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of signal flow.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of stage management procedures and safety; electrical, cable paths, storage etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting / troubleshooting devices such as laptop computers, desktop computers,conference room display TV’s or projection based displays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in the basic installation, configuration and operation of computer operating systems,applications and hardware for Mac, PC, networks and servers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to move/lift 50+ lbs. and set up stage, audio, video and lighting equipment with care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A drive to continually learn new skills and technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time Hourly (Non-Exempt)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: Production Manager&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Campus Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt; at Christ Fellowship’s Boynton Beach Location provides administrative and ministerial coordination support to the campus. You are outgoing, logistically strong, and passionate about checklists. You exemplify our core value ‘Passion For People’ to the fullest. This is a full-time salary (exempt) position reporting to the Campus Pastor, including work on weekends and some nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Multiply volunteer teams by building relationships with and supporting their team leaders. These teams include, but not necessarily limited to:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Service Support Teams - Logistics (Service Prep Team), Service Coordinators, Data Entry, Baptism, Free Coffee Team, Dream Team Hospitality, Event Hospitality, Pop up Shop, Translation Team, Social Media and Photography&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operations Team - Medical Team, Security Team, Contributions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully supporting these volunteer teams by resourcing them with materials, technology, training, moral encouragement, and your illuminating smile.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continually cultivating (alongside our campus pastor) our relationships with multiple Palm Beach County Organizations (School District, Sheriff’s Office, Palm Beach County, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile monthly departmental expenses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all logistical aspects of campus events (i.e. Easter/Christmas, Sisterhood Nights, etc).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Upkeep the look and feel of the campus environments – channel your favorite inner HGTV design show.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in leading and developing staff and volunteers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptionally organized with an operational and administrative mind – we run on checklists and deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication abilities with a high capacity for prioritizing – we work at warp speeds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone with an eye for details and the capacity to see the big picture – creativity, collaboration and innovation are key.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Salary (Exempt)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: Campus Pastor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Conferences &amp;amp; Events Manager &lt;/strong&gt;serves as the Event Logistics Lead for all conferences and church wide (global) events. This role would be responsible for coordinating all event logistics and cross-functional efforts for conferences and global events. This position reports to the Director of Campus Logistics &amp;amp; Events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONFERENCES &amp;amp; EVENTS RESPONSIBILITIES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the event logistics lead for all conferences and church-wide events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Event Visionary &amp;amp; Ministry Lead to coordinate event timelines, event meetings and event logistics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work cross-functionally with the Events Lead Team that will focus on event timelines, event details, event communication, event budget, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the budget Subject Matter Expert (SME) for the Global Events budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create event templates and timelines that can be used for ministry and campus specific events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a team of consistent team leads for conferences and global events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and lead a Conferences &amp;amp; Events Dream Team by implementing our SERVE Model&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage our Brushfire ticketing system to set up ticket sales, promo codes, seating, etc.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the liaison with the City of Palm Beach Gardens for event permits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor’s degree preferred.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-4 years experience planning and executing events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with project &amp;amp; task management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working cross-functionally and collaboratively with other departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly developed interpersonal communication to provide exceptional care and concern while prioritizing and adjusting to multiple moving parts in a fast paced-setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Salary (Exempt)&lt;br&gt;Reporting to: Central Director of Campus Logistics &amp;amp; Events&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Facilities Crew &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;supports the campus pre- and post-events. This will include the setup and teardown of weekend services as well as special events. This role works with various Christ Fellowship staff and volunteers. All candidates must be available to work a flexible schedule, including nights and weekends.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Lead and develop volunteer teams to help meet the high demand of ministry needs at Christ Fellowship.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Fully supporting these volunteer teams by resourcing them with materials, technology, and training.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Set up and tear-down of facilities for services, meetings, classrooms, conferences, events, etc., on and off campus.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Maintain the building with custodial support, as well as minor repairs and general maintenance.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Support and enforce all policies of Christ Fellowship, such as OSHA rules, church health and safety regulations and guidelines, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Logistically supporting many aspects of large campus events.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;High School Diploma&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CERTIFICATION OR LICENSES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Florida Driver&#39;s License&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;3 - 5 years of relevant&amp;nbsp; experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Requires a knowledge of cleaning products and safety&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Must be able to physically lift 40 lbs. or more&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Must be able to stand for long periods of time and be able to bend, stoop, carry, and reach&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Classification: Full-time, hourly (non-exempt)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Reporting to: Facilities Manager &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Facilities Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;at the Belle Glade location&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;assists in the care and upkeep of all buildings and grounds. The Facilities Specialist cares for the day-to-day maintenance of buildings and grounds, partners with staff, and builds volunteer teams to serve alongside them. All candidates must be available to work a flexible schedule, some weekends, and holidays. This is a part-time, hourly (non-exempt) position, working 25 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and execute all facilities responsibilities as the dedicated on-site staff member.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, develop, and grow facilities volunteer teams, providing training, resources, and encouragement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and communicate weekly team schedules to coordinate coverage and support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee and actively participate in setup and tear-down for services, meetings, classrooms, conferences, and special events both on and off campus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain buildings and grounds, including custodial support, minor repairs, and general maintenance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor building conditions regularly and proactively address issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond to work orders, prioritize tasks, and ensure timely completion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate vehicles, power tools, and equipment as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide logistical support for campus events, including DIESEL, Sisterhood, Easter/Christmas, and CF Conference.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with emergency responses and alarm calls as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and enforce all Christ Fellowship policies, including OSHA regulations and church health and safety guidelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with vendors for repairs, maintenance, and other facility needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other tasks and projects assigned by campus leadership or Central Facilities to ensure smooth campus operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High School Diploma&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate&#39;s Degree or Higher preferred, but not required&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CERTIFICATION OR LICENSES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Florida Driver&#39;s License&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CDL preferred but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;OSHA Certifications strongly preferred&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3 - 5 years of relevant experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Part-Time, Hourly (Non-Exempt), 25 hours per week&lt;br&gt;Reporting to: Campus Pastor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Human Resources Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;at Christ Fellowship oversees core HR operations, including payroll processing, benefits administration, compliance, and HRIS data integrity. Reporting directly to the HR Systems Administrator, this role delivers high-touch HR services to over 400 employees across multiple campus locations. The ideal candidate serves as a reliable liaison between staff and insurance providers while ensuring absolute accuracy in our employment and payroll systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Payroll &amp;amp; HRIS Administration&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather, verify, and input employee data into ADP Workforce Now to execute accurate and timely payroll runs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain real-time accuracy of organizational charts, personnel files, and system data within the HRIS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage employee lifecycle data entry, tracking hires, terminations, transfers, leaves, and promotions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the automated employment verification system and handle data reporting/analysis as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits &amp;amp; Leave Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer comprehensive employee benefit plans, including Health Savings Accounts (HSA), Flexible Spending Accounts (FSA), COBRA, and disability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary liaison with the insurance broker and mediate benefit-related inquiries or claims issues for staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage leave administration (FMLA, short/long-term disability), tracking timelines and coordinating return-to-work plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;File and monitor workers&#39; compensation claims to ensure compliance and timely resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Employee Lifecycle&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct monthly and annual compliance audits for insurance plans, ACA, and EEOC reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and facilitate payroll and benefits orientations for new hires to ensure a smooth onboarding process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct &quot;Years of Service&quot; check-ins to support employee retention and gather feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cultivate professional, productive relationships with vendors and industry partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Undergraduate Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1-3 years of relevant work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of principles and procedures for compensation and benefits, labor relations, and personnel information systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of business and management principles involved in strategic planning, human resources modeling, and coordination of people and resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Hourly (Non-Exempt)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: Human Resources System Administrator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Christ Fellowship&lt;strong&gt; Kids Ministry Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; provides support and care for every aspect of the Children’s Ministry area.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involved in selecting and equipping a volunteer team so they can thrive in their assigned roles on the Christ Fellowship Kids team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure weekend resources are prepared and distributed in preparation for the weekend experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting weekend and midweek programming as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to Central Team initiative development and implementation as directed by and in cooperation with Central Kids Directors and team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending weekly staff meetings and Department meetings as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a PHASE expert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in progress; a focus in education/ministry is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with 1 year in a kids’ ministry environment, either as staff or volunteer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Part-time (25 hours) Hourly (non - exempt) position including weekends and some week nights.&lt;br&gt;Reporting to: Kids Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Christ Fellowship &lt;strong&gt;Kids Ministry Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; provides support and care across all aspects of the Children’s Ministry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involved in selecting and equipping a volunteer team so they can thrive in their assigned roles on the Christ Fellowship Kids team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure midweek resources are prepared and distributed in preparation for the midweek experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting weekend and midweek programming as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to Central Team initiative development and implementation as directed by and in cooperation with Central Kids Directors and team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending weekly staff meetings and Department meetings as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a PHASE expert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in progress; a focus in education/ministry is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with 1 year in a kids’ ministry environment, either as staff or volunteer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Hourly (non-exempt) position, including weekends and some weeknights.&lt;br&gt;Reporting to: Kids Ministry Director&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Christ Fellowship Kids Ministry Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; provides support and care for every aspect of the kids ministry. This is a part-time, hourly (non-exempt) position, working 20 hours per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Involved in selecting and equipping a volunteer team so they can thrive in their assigned roles on the Christ Fellowship Kids team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure weekend resources are prepared and distributed in preparation for the weekend experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting weekend and midweek programming as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to Central Team initiative development and implementation as directed by and in cooperation with Central Kids Directors and team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending weekly staff meetings and Department meetings as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a PHASE expert.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree in progress; a focus in education/ministry is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with 1 year in a kids’ ministry environment, either as staff or volunteer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Part-time, Hourly (non-exempt) position, working 20 hours per week, including weekends and some week nights.&lt;br&gt;Reporting to: Kids Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Christ Fellowship &lt;strong&gt;Kids Ministry Director&lt;/strong&gt; provides leadership and care for all things Christ Fellowship Kids from babies to 4th grade.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading and developing staff teams and volunteers so that they are operating in their strengths and being most effective in their roles on the Christ Fellowship Kids team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating and maintaining a strong “ALL IN”&amp;nbsp; team culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Growing campus attendance by implementing our Central Kids Team strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the proper implementation of curriculum, policies, and procedures as directed by the Central Kids Team. (Weekends and Kids U)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring volunteers and staff members align with our mission, vision, and values.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct the implementation of milestones (i.e. Spiritual Steps).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to or assisting with Central Kids initiatives as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending weekly CF staff meetings and Christ Fellowship Kids department meetings, as required.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capturing kids and family stories of life change – grab a box of tissues for this!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A college graduate, preferably with a ministry degree, kid’s ministry related or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 years of leadership experience in kids’ ministry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-Time, Salary (Exempt), including weekends and some nights.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: Campus Pastor&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Christ Fellowship &lt;strong&gt;Kids Ministry Volunteer&amp;nbsp;Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt; supports the Kids Ministry&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;by ensuring the effective implementation of the volunteer onboarding and placement process and, at times, assisting the Kids Ministry Director with various administrative responsibilities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the volunteer onboarding process in accordance with central objectives, processes, and philosophy, including our SERVE (volunteer onboarding) strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and help implement volunteer recruiting, training, and appreciation strategies and initiatives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting Area Coordinators as they build their volunteer teams.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the supervision of midweek programming during the week as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create a memorable “full of fun” impression by exceeding guests’ expectations in the Family Check-In experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the process that ensures we care for new families and help them find community at the campus.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the campus’s Connections (“Next Steps”) team to ensure cohesion between the Campus Welcome Team volunteers and the Kids Welcome Team volunteers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contributing to the development and implementation of Central Team initiatives, as directed by and in cooperation with Central Kids Ministry Directors and the team.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attending weekly staff meetings and department meetings as directed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensuring the overall weekend experience for kids is done with excellence in a safe, fun, meaningful, and engaging environment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;College graduate or degree in progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced with 1 year in a kids’ ministry environment, either as staff or volunteer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Salary (Exempt) position, including weekends and some nights.&lt;br&gt;Reporting to: Kids Ministry Director&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;The &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missions Coordinator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; at Christ Fellowship oversees the planning and execution of&amp;nbsp; Missions events, local and international missions in a fast-paced, diverse, multi-site ministry environment. Our Missions Coordinators will organize and oversee multiple, concurrent projects from volunteer recruitment through project logistics and budget stewardship and reconciliation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Serves as primary point of contact and owner for all activities related to local missions, international missions&amp;nbsp; and&amp;nbsp; missions events and opportunities at the campus level.&amp;nbsp; Expectation would be that you would lead one international mission trip a year.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Collaborates with Campus Pastors and Coordinators to undertake projects in local communities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Recruits, interviews and trains volunteer team leaders and members.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Provides leadership, direction, and community to volunteer and support teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Proactively plans, schedules and implements complex logistics of events and missions – from start to finish.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Collaborates with community partners and support teams to implement projects with excellence, in the constraints of timing and budget.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Accomplishes assigned projects through other ministry staff; utilizing highly developed communication (written and verbal), project management, time management and collaboration skills.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Responds to regularly occurring requests for information.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Organizes and prioritizes large volumes of information and calls.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Evaluates and reports on goals, objectives, and metrics of Missions’ efforts.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Bachelor’s degree in a related area of study&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;3-5 years&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Classification: Full-time | Salaried (exempt)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;flexible schedule, including nights, weekends and occasional overnight travel.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Supervisor: Missions Director&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Production Assistant &lt;/strong&gt;in Christ Fellowship’s Campus Production Team&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;provides overall general assistance to the Production Manager in the coordination of campus production logistics, operation of campus production systems, and volunteer onboarding/care.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain the process of recruiting, onboarding, scheduling, and training volunteers.  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate weekly check-ins with production volunteers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate and troubleshoot production equipment across audio, video, and lighting systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the preparation and transfers of content for weekends and events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with the management of supplies and inventory.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Completed or undergraduate degree in progress&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CERTIFICATES&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; LICENSES and/or REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational knowledge in at least one production discipline; audio, video (preferred), or lighting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience loading in/out and setting/striking production equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1-3 years of relevant experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Hourly (Non-Exempt)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: Production Manager&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SUMMARY:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Production&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Systems Engineer &lt;/strong&gt;at Christ Fellowship manages&amp;nbsp; the Production (audio, video, lighting) based technical infrastructure across all campus locations, and ensures that system performance is optimal for each application. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DUTIES:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve incidents involving audio, RF, video, lighting, communications, networking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and maintain LED video wall displays and associated processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain device network connectivity, IP tables, and IP organization.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrate new systems upgrades and expansions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research equipment and develop proposals that pertain to AVL projects at different campuses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain engineering and one line drawings for each project and location.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain contingency inventory and deploying equipment.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor technical systems to ensure its stability and conduct preventative maintenance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrative duties such as reconciling vendor invoices and monthly expense reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend scheduled programming and review meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve at scheduled CF events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Look for opportunities to further develop your skill through industry relevant education.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Computer Science, Electronic Engineering, Information Technology, or related field.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CERTIFICATES&lt;/strong&gt;,&lt;strong&gt; and REQUIRED TECHNICAL SKILLS:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven technical aptitude.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough knowledge of Production based electrical systems and requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operational knowledge of foundational production systems: Audio, video &amp;amp; lighting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of information technology systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of network based production protocols.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of control systems is a plus (Q-Sys, Crestron, Kramer).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in interpreting and referencing one line/design drawings.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safety certifications ETCP, ESTA, USITT a plus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CTS, CTS-I, or CTS-D a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3+ years’ experience of operating, integrating, and maintaining Production systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB SPECS:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Classification: Full-time, Salary (Exempt)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to: Engineering Director&lt;/p&gt;

