&lt;li&gt;Looking after agendas, mailings, calendars, attendance, and other tasks, which may include reconciling department financial statements, and tracking ministry budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;EDUCATION:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;College graduate, or degree in progress, preferably in a related field of ministry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RELEVANT WORK EXPERIENCE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in student ministry.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in building and leading teams or volunteers, including recruiting, training and mentoring.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient with computers, and social media, and able to quickly become proficient in new technology formats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
